The paper deals with online market mechanisms and competitive analysis, which are topics commonly studied in the subfield of game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.EC). The use of prior knowledge and distributions suggests a focus on probability and statistics (cs.IT), while the study of posted-price mechanisms and the optimization of profit and social welfare relate to market algorithms (cs.MA) and data structures (cs.DS).
